# Backup/Restore Script Configuration

# AUTOMATIC LOADING:
# The script automatically sources this file if named .env and placed in the
# 1. Copy and secure this file:
#    cp .env.example .env
#    chmod 600 .env
# 2. Update `.env` file if needed:
#    nano .env  (or use your preferred editor)
# 3. Source the env file.
#    source .env
# 4. Start using the script:
#    ./backup-restore.sh <import|export>...

# IMPORTANT: 
# - If you changed the OpenSearch password during deployment, set it here
# - Default password works for standard deployments but NOT recommended for production

# Uncomment and set your password:
# OPENSEARCH_PASSWORD=YourCustomPasswordHere

